author: whitlock
msg: Fix DynamicSetSOAPMethodAttrTest2 test by not testing adding duplicate attributes.

Change free(m_pCall) in many testcases to delete m_pCall, since m_pCall was new'ed. This caused the AnyObject testcases to break since now ~Call failed during ~Param. The fix to this is to not delete the atorage for the AnyObject since it is the user's storage and the AnyObject has never brrn cloned. It is up to the application to delete this storage.

author: dicka
msg: The mix of cout and printf statements can result in output becoming out of sequence on some platforms.  To resolve this place an ffliush(stdout) after printf, before using a cout.

author: dicka
msg: Modifications to string based XSD testcases, due to recent changes to the memory management paradigm.
This requires the "new"ing of strings being used in complex types, but not deleting, as this will be carried out by the complex type destructor.
